1
00:00:00,580 --> 00:00:05,800
<i>[A Story to Read When You First Fall in Love]</i>

2
00:00:08,010 --> 00:00:10,700
<i>[Hanaekai, A Cram School Specialized in the University of Tokyo]</i>

3
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:11,790
What is the meaning of this?

4
00:00:11,790 --> 00:00:15,530
Hanaekai is a cram school specialized in the University of Tokyo

5
00:00:15,530 --> 00:00:17,910
that boasts an eighty percent passing rate.

6
00:00:17,910 --> 00:00:21,070
They only accept students from prestigious schools.

7
00:00:21,070 --> 00:00:24,420
But they made an exception for you and allowed your enrollment.

8
00:00:24,420 --> 00:00:26,040
That's nonsense. Harumi, you're my-

9
00:00:26,040 --> 00:00:27,930
Only three subjects in the science course.

10
00:00:27,930 --> 00:00:30,280
You'll study the rest with me.

11
00:00:30,280 --> 00:00:33,070
I'm not capable enough to teach you mathematics.

12
00:00:33,070 --> 00:00:37,130
We only have a month till the last mock exam in November.

13
00:00:37,130 --> 00:00:40,400
You have to improve your academic level significantly by then.

14
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:44,160
Otherwise, you won't get into the University of Tokyo.

15
00:00:46,060 --> 00:00:48,370
I told you, didn't I?

16
00:00:48,370 --> 00:00:52,000
I'll make sure you'll get in by all means.

17
00:00:53,480 --> 00:00:57,090
Don't you wish to get in right after high school?

18
00:00:57,090 --> 00:00:59,220
<i>I can't wait two or three years.</i>

19
00:00:59,220 --> 00:01:03,500
<i>Because I have something to tell you after I pass the exam.</i>

20
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:07,650
I've already discussed this with your father.

21
00:01:07,650 --> 00:01:12,490
The question is, will you be able to handle attending two cram schools.

22
00:01:13,360 --> 00:01:17,730
Why don't we go to a trial enrollment first?

23
00:01:18,830 --> 00:01:24,980
<i>Timing and Subtitles brought to you by
</i>ðŸ’–True Love TeamðŸ’–<i>@Viki.com</i>

24
00:01:25,660 --> 00:01:27,650
Fine.

25
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:32,870
<i>Wow, it seems so far.</i>

26
00:01:32,870 --> 00:01:34,440
Yokohama is surely different from Tokyo.

27
00:01:34,440 --> 00:01:36,360
In what way?

28
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:38,430
Girls in Yokohama are cuter.

29
00:01:38,430 --> 00:01:39,810
I think you're right.

30
00:01:39,810 --> 00:01:42,310
I came along because I was free.

31
00:01:42,310 --> 00:01:45,110
I envy you, Kyo. Are you attending a cram school here?

32
00:01:45,110 --> 00:01:47,590
- I haven't decided yet.
- Really?

33
00:01:47,590 --> 00:01:50,190
It's the building over there.

34
00:01:51,530 --> 00:01:53,640
<i>Harumi-sensei!</i>

35
00:01:59,070 --> 00:02:01,380
What a cutie.

36
00:02:01,380 --> 00:02:02,880
Momota-sensei.

37
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:05,020
A teacher?

38
00:02:05,650 --> 00:02:09,390
Nice to meet you all. I'm Momota of Hanaekai.

39
00:02:09,390 --> 00:02:11,520
Which one of you is Yuri?

40
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:12,880
I'm Yuri.

41
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:14,660
Is that you?

42
00:02:17,370 --> 00:02:21,260
He has pink hair, but he's a hard worker and motivated.

43
00:02:21,260 --> 00:02:24,420
I know. You mentioned that before.

44
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,310
You're good-looking.

45
00:02:28,310 --> 00:02:32,490
Guys, don't you think she's a true beauty?

46
00:02:32,490 --> 00:02:34,110
And elegant.

47
00:02:34,110 --> 00:02:37,060
She is the perfect description of a capable woman.

48
00:02:37,060 --> 00:02:38,990
Teacher, how old are you?

49
00:02:38,990 --> 00:02:41,240
I'm twenty-seven.

50
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:42,800
Twenty-seven? You're so young.

51
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:47,050
I assumed all teachers in cram schools for the University of Tokyo were old geezers.

52
00:02:47,050 --> 00:02:49,140
Or, old ladies like Junko-sensei.

53
00:02:49,140 --> 00:02:51,300
Watch it.

54
00:02:51,300 --> 00:02:53,770
I'll be going now.

55
00:02:53,770 --> 00:02:56,920
Would you like to visit our school?

56
00:02:56,920 --> 00:02:59,680
- I'm in.
- Me, too.

57
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:03,240
Wow.

58
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:06,690
It's huge.

59
00:03:06,690 --> 00:03:08,840
If this is the cram school specialized in the University of Tokyo,

60
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:10,260
did you graduate from the University of Tokyo as well?

61
00:03:10,260 --> 00:03:12,370
I graduated from UCL.

62
00:03:12,370 --> 00:03:14,510
UC...

63
00:03:14,510 --> 00:03:17,190
It's University College London.

64
00:03:17,190 --> 00:03:19,690
Many Nobel Prize laureates graduated from UCL.

65
00:03:19,690 --> 00:03:21,770
It's one of the best university in the world.

66
00:03:21,770 --> 00:03:24,250
Is that better than the University of Tokyo?

67
00:03:24,250 --> 00:03:26,390
How impressive.

68
00:03:26,390 --> 00:03:30,130
Where are we going now?

69
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:34,270
<i>Good education, fine career,</i>

70
00:03:34,270 --> 00:03:37,460
<i>youth, and money...</i>

71
00:03:37,460 --> 00:03:41,840
<i>She has everything I'm lacking of.</i>

72
00:03:44,290 --> 00:03:47,140
Momota-sensei, why have you decided to become a teacher?

73
00:03:47,140 --> 00:03:49,850
Let's not talk about me.

74
00:03:51,050 --> 00:03:53,330
This is the self-study room.

75
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:56,170
Very spacious.

76
00:03:56,170 --> 00:03:57,420
We have some complimentary drinks.

77
00:03:57,420 --> 00:04:00,260
- Can I have some?
- Seriously?

78
00:04:00,260 --> 00:04:03,100
Some students use an app for studying,

79
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:05,180
so we're lending out these tablets.

80
00:04:05,180 --> 00:04:09,300
There is a nap room right next to here.

81
00:04:09,300 --> 00:04:12,700
This place is totally different from your school, Junko-sensei.

82
00:04:12,700 --> 00:04:15,760
I only need a teacher and a desk for studying.

83
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:18,480
Who needs the over-the-top facility?

84
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:21,760
- Yuri.
- I like that.

85
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:25,050
I appreciate your straight-forwardness.

86
00:04:25,050 --> 00:04:26,920
I'm sorry.

87
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:31,120
Once you study with us, you will appreciate what we offer here.

88
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:34,980
Why not take a lesson here, Yuri?

89
00:04:34,980 --> 00:04:37,270
I'll leave him in your care.

90
00:04:41,290 --> 00:04:44,960
I can take it from here. Follow me.

91
00:04:55,210 --> 00:04:56,950
Good luck.

92
00:05:03,450 --> 00:05:05,230
How nice.

93
00:05:05,230 --> 00:05:07,750
If I could study under her, I would come to the cram school.

94
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:09,820
I know, right?

95
00:05:11,230 --> 00:05:13,140
Zunko-sensei?

96
00:05:13,140 --> 00:05:16,300
I feel like a mama bird sending off her chick leaving the nest.

97
00:05:16,300 --> 00:05:18,470
A mama bird?

98
00:05:18,470 --> 00:05:20,550
- Let's go home.
- Okay.

99
00:05:20,550 --> 00:05:21,850
How envious.

100
00:05:21,850 --> 00:05:24,510
- Let's go.
- So envious.

101
00:05:36,350 --> 00:05:38,890
What's wrong with her? She's scaring me.

102
00:05:38,890 --> 00:05:42,910
She looks burnt out and turned into ashes...

103
00:05:42,910 --> 00:05:45,550
Like a boxer.
<i>(T/N: Referring to a character from Tomorrow's Joe.)</i>

104
00:05:45,550 --> 00:05:48,130
Oh, she moved.

105
00:05:53,270 --> 00:05:55,030
Harumi-sensei?

106
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:57,980
Harumi-sensei!

107
00:05:59,590 --> 00:06:02,460
- Yes?
- Don't forget to breathe, okay?

108
00:06:03,380 --> 00:06:07,410
I heard Yuri is taking some classes at Hanaekai.

109
00:06:07,410 --> 00:06:08,940
- That's right.
- Hanaekai?

110
00:06:08,940 --> 00:06:12,950
Yes. He's studying three subject in sciences and math

111
00:06:12,950 --> 00:06:15,560
under the most popular teacher named Momota.

112
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:18,040
Oh, that's why...

113
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:20,150
Is there a problem?

114
00:06:20,150 --> 00:06:21,720
No, not at all.

115
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:23,330
This is rather fortunate.

116
00:06:23,330 --> 00:06:25,670
If he passes the college exam by chance,

117
00:06:25,670 --> 00:06:28,040
we can take credit for it.

118
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:31,190
Besides, I'm very pleased

119
00:06:31,190 --> 00:06:34,210
that you've become a fine teacher who can make a rational decision

120
00:06:34,210 --> 00:06:37,030
by setting your emotions aside.

121
00:06:37,030 --> 00:06:40,040
- Manager...
- However,

122
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:45,240
if Yuri is a fine student who can make a rational decision,

123
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:50,470
he may say he'll switch to the other school to learn his humanities subjects.

124
00:06:54,670 --> 00:06:58,510
<i>That's right. There is no time for me to slack off.</i>

125
00:06:58,510 --> 00:07:02,100
<i>I ought to do whatever I can to improve myself.</i>

126
00:07:03,610 --> 00:07:05,530
Okay. That's all for today's lesson.

127
00:07:05,530 --> 00:07:07,810
If you have any questions, feel free to ask.

128
00:07:07,810 --> 00:07:09,170
I have nothing but questions.

129
00:07:09,170 --> 00:07:12,070
- Excuse me, Momota-sensei...
- I have a question, too.

130
00:07:12,070 --> 00:07:16,270
Okay. I'll take a question one by one.

131
00:07:16,270 --> 00:07:18,140
Let's start with you.

132
00:07:18,140 --> 00:07:20,430
Get in a line.

133
00:07:20,430 --> 00:07:24,020
<i>Get in a line.</i>

134
00:07:24,020 --> 00:07:26,240
What a conspicuous hair.

135
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:32,060
- Yeah.
- Are you fond of Momo-chan-sensei as well?

136
00:07:32,610 --> 00:07:34,020
What?

137
00:07:34,630 --> 00:07:36,380
She's a cutie, isn't she?

138
00:07:36,380 --> 00:07:38,260
She's pretty and graduated from UCL.

139
00:07:38,260 --> 00:07:41,800
Her classes are very easy to understand.

140
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:43,590
Which school do you go to?

141
00:07:43,590 --> 00:07:44,960
Minami High.

142
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:46,810
Minami High?

143
00:07:50,110 --> 00:07:51,570
Yuri.

144
00:07:51,570 --> 00:07:55,400
You need a supplementary lesson. Wait for me at the self-study room.

145
00:07:56,580 --> 00:07:58,040
Okay?

146
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:02,070
Sure.

147
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:06,110
Hey, what kind of school is this? It's crazy.

148
00:08:06,110 --> 00:08:10,090
It's crazy all right because it's a specialized school for the University of Tokyo.

149
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:14,410
Not that. Students are flirting with the teacher.

150
00:08:14,410 --> 00:08:16,450
<i>Well, she is a popular teacher.</i>

151
00:08:16,450 --> 00:08:19,690
More than eighty percent of her students

152
00:08:19,690 --> 00:08:22,470
passed the college exam in the past three years.

153
00:08:22,470 --> 00:08:26,300
<i>I've never thought she would take you under her wings.</i>

154
00:08:26,300 --> 00:08:28,360
I was shocked how young she is, but

155
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:30,750
she is the real deal when it comes to teaching sciences majors of the University of Tokyo.

156
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:35,020
I'm exhausted from studying with so many students in one class.

157
00:08:35,020 --> 00:08:36,390
That's right.

158
00:08:36,390 --> 00:08:40,190
Be thankful to study under an unpopular teacher like me.

159
00:08:41,380 --> 00:08:44,220
I want you to teach me the science and math.

160
00:08:44,220 --> 00:08:46,250
I told you.

161
00:08:46,250 --> 00:08:48,390
I'm not good enough.

162
00:08:50,110 --> 00:08:51,720
Yuri.

163
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:54,460
I told you to wait at the self-study room, didn't I?

164
00:08:54,460 --> 00:08:56,080
Right.

165
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:02,710
"C" and "L" have three interceptions,

166
00:09:02,710 --> 00:09:07,300
it means there are two interceptions other than the origin.

167
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:11,030
Since "X equal one minus M",

168
00:09:11,030 --> 00:09:15,360
so "M" is greater than zero, but less than one.

169
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:17,270
That makes sense.

170
00:09:19,610 --> 00:09:22,210
It's not embarrassing to ask what you don't know.

171
00:09:22,210 --> 00:09:25,410
So ask me anything, okay?

172
00:09:25,410 --> 00:09:28,000
Excuse me, could you help me with this?

173
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:31,600
- Sorry, Shimazaki. I'll help you later.
- What?

174
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:34,790
Now let's do some practice problems.

175
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:45,050
Were you talking to Harumi-sensei over the phone earlier?

176
00:09:45,910 --> 00:09:47,570
Yeah.

177
00:09:48,220 --> 00:09:50,840
You must trust her a lot.

178
00:09:53,220 --> 00:09:55,270
Your hair really is amazing!

179
00:09:55,270 --> 00:09:58,130
How often do you dye it?

180
00:10:03,700 --> 00:10:07,030
Then how about you try solving this problem?

181
00:10:23,340 --> 00:10:25,170
The hard part of the listening portion of the exam...

182
00:10:25,170 --> 00:10:28,890
is its length, not its complexity.

183
00:10:28,890 --> 00:10:31,200
To improve your concentration

184
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:33,950
so you can listen to a three to five minute long English paragraph,

185
00:10:33,950 --> 00:10:36,050
you should listen to English for 30 minutes

186
00:10:36,050 --> 00:10:37,920
every day until the mock exam.

187
00:10:37,920 --> 00:10:41,520
Right now I'm making listening tracks for you to practice.

188
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:43,170
Okay.

189
00:10:47,460 --> 00:10:49,580
How are things at Hanaekai?

190
00:10:49,580 --> 00:10:52,380
Is everything okay? Can you keep up?

191
00:10:52,380 --> 00:10:54,380
- If there's anything you don't understand-
- It's okay.

192
00:10:54,380 --> 00:10:56,670
There's tons of homework,

193
00:10:56,670 --> 00:10:59,380
the teacher gives me easier questions

194
00:10:59,380 --> 00:11:02,960
but it's also challenging for me.

195
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:04,310
I see.

196
00:11:04,310 --> 00:11:06,260
She is kind of annoying,

197
00:11:06,260 --> 00:11:09,400
but she's just as good as you said.

198
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:12,530
I'm glad to hear that.

199
00:11:33,220 --> 00:11:37,140
<i>[A Story to Read When You First Fall in Love]</i>

200
00:11:37,140 --> 00:11:41,480
<i>[Episode 7]</i>
So fate really does exist!

201
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:43,780
<i>I'm Kanbei and he's Hideyoshi.</i>

202
00:11:43,780 --> 00:11:46,890
So we're a perfect match even in the Feudal Warlord Fortune-Teller.

203
00:11:46,890 --> 00:11:51,370
Even though he's an unsuccessful dancer, he's got money!

204
00:11:51,370 --> 00:11:54,990
We met when I was leaving your high school class reunion.

205
00:11:54,990 --> 00:11:59,020
I told him I'm a divorced working mom. I had to change clothes today, too!

206
00:11:59,020 --> 00:12:00,350
So that's your costume?

207
00:12:00,350 --> 00:12:01,380
What do you mean by costume?

208
00:12:01,380 --> 00:12:05,310
He'll figure it out soon if he's as observant as I am.

209
00:12:05,310 --> 00:12:09,310
Halloween is coming up. You should host a costume party.

210
00:12:09,310 --> 00:12:11,480
My bar tripled the profits on that day.

211
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:13,940
- Tripled?
- Yes.

212
00:12:13,940 --> 00:12:16,530
Junko, were you even listening?

213
00:12:16,530 --> 00:12:18,610
Sorry, I wasn't.

214
00:12:18,610 --> 00:12:22,330
Isn't Yuri taking fewer classes with you? Can't you take a break?

215
00:12:22,330 --> 00:12:25,370
It's the opposite! Now that he's going to a new cram school

216
00:12:25,370 --> 00:12:28,800
to keep him from finding out my shortcoming,

217
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:32,520
- I have to work till my bones turn to dust and pee blood!
- What?

218
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:37,190
Be sure to pee normal, not blood, Junko.

219
00:12:37,950 --> 00:12:41,190
I know I was the one who suggested it, but

220
00:12:41,190 --> 00:12:44,020
I hate myself for not being able to teach him all subjects.

221
00:12:44,020 --> 00:12:47,400
The teacher at Hanaekai is only twenty-seven,

222
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:48,870
and she's superior to me in every aspect.

223
00:12:48,870 --> 00:12:53,750
- Twenty-seven, the Momo-chan-sensei?
- Yeah.

224
00:12:55,420 --> 00:13:00,170
I can't tell if you're oblivious or over-thinking.

225
00:13:00,170 --> 00:13:02,940
That is so-called jealous.

226
00:13:02,940 --> 00:13:05,930
- As a teacher, and as a woman.
- What?

227
00:13:06,780 --> 00:13:11,100
Jealous. You're afraid of losing Yurihei.

228
00:13:12,060 --> 00:13:13,990
What are you talking about?

229
00:13:13,990 --> 00:13:18,170
That's not it. I'm just telling you I'm working hard, too.

230
00:13:18,170 --> 00:13:20,550
I don't have the leisure to relax here.

231
00:13:20,550 --> 00:13:22,630
Sorry. I'm going home and work.

232
00:13:22,630 --> 00:13:24,190
What? Are you leaving?

233
00:13:24,190 --> 00:13:25,810
Yes, I am.

234
00:13:25,810 --> 00:13:30,320
Sorry, I'm late! What? Are you leaving, Junko?

235
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:33,360
You can eat my share.

236
00:13:34,040 --> 00:13:36,110
- Bye.
- Hold on a second.

237
00:13:36,110 --> 00:13:40,030
You know... about what you said the other day.

238
00:13:40,030 --> 00:13:43,030
"I didn't want anybody to find that out, especially you, Masashi."

239
00:13:43,030 --> 00:13:46,680
I want to know about that more in details.

240
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:49,340
<i>I didn't want anybody to find that out, especially you, Masashi.</i>

241
00:13:49,340 --> 00:13:51,380
<i>Especially me?</i>

242
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:55,280
Can we talk about that some other time?

243
00:13:55,280 --> 00:13:57,960
I want to explain it to you properly.

244
00:13:59,030 --> 00:14:01,870
Sure, yeah.

245
00:14:01,870 --> 00:14:03,940
You're absolutely right.

246
00:14:05,180 --> 00:14:07,490
Bye.

247
00:14:07,490 --> 00:14:09,860
Thanks for coming.

248
00:14:09,860 --> 00:14:11,980
- Take care.
- Okay.

249
00:14:11,980 --> 00:14:13,940
- Welcome.
- Welcome.

250
00:14:13,940 --> 00:14:16,000
What's up?

251
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:20,240
It's heartwarming to see how clueless you are.

252
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:21,560
What do you mean?

253
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:23,590
Jealousy is the beginning of love.

254
00:14:23,590 --> 00:14:25,020
You might be in trouble.

255
00:14:25,020 --> 00:14:26,300
In trouble?

256
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:31,960
Junko sent Yuri to attend a cram school in Yokohama that specialized in the University of Tokyo.

