00:30:59,590 --> 00:31:02,580
I just made some for your father anyway.

505
00:31:16,080 --> 00:31:18,790
Did something good happen, Dear?

506
00:31:20,070 --> 00:31:21,430
Would you like some coffee?

507
00:31:21,430 --> 00:31:24,080
No thanks. I won't be able to sleep.

508
00:31:24,080 --> 00:31:29,320
Oh! Uncle Kazuhiko's daughter, Kana is getting married soon.

509
00:31:29,320 --> 00:31:32,770
Your mom's youngest brother?

510
00:31:32,770 --> 00:31:37,750
My mom overjoyed on the phone that she was invited to the wedding.

511
00:31:37,750 --> 00:31:38,720
Which college did he go to?

512
00:31:38,720 --> 00:31:43,910
He was her senior of the same class. So law school, I bet.

513
00:31:43,910 --> 00:31:47,360
You and your sister both went to the University of Tokyo.

514
00:31:47,360 --> 00:31:49,620
Masashi did, too.

515
00:31:49,620 --> 00:31:51,610
Only Junko didn't.

516
00:31:52,180 --> 00:31:55,040
Maybe you shouldn't compare her to other people.

517
00:31:55,040 --> 00:32:00,820
It's because I failed as a wife and a mother,

518
00:32:02,360 --> 00:32:06,630
no wonder your mom hates me.

519
00:32:09,770 --> 00:32:11,690
It's so cold!

520
00:32:20,310 --> 00:32:21,950
Yuka.

521
00:32:23,130 --> 00:32:25,000
Kazuma?

522
00:32:27,300 --> 00:32:29,910
I was in the neighborhood.

523
00:32:30,900 --> 00:32:33,140
Running errands...

524
00:32:38,620 --> 00:32:40,340
Are you okay?

525
00:32:44,410 --> 00:32:46,650
I'm getting by.

526
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:51,280
I ended up moving back to my parents' home.

527
00:32:52,170 --> 00:32:54,010
How's your dad?

528
00:32:56,990 --> 00:32:59,890
His illness is getting worse.

529
00:32:59,890 --> 00:33:02,350
That's one of the reason I moved back.

530
00:33:02,350 --> 00:33:05,070
I'm his only daughter.

531
00:33:06,260 --> 00:33:09,320
I haven't been able to visit him...

532
00:33:09,320 --> 00:33:10,860
I'm sorry.

533
00:33:10,860 --> 00:33:16,080
It's fine. He'll just get worked up if he sees you.

534
00:33:19,900 --> 00:33:21,490
Hey...

535
00:33:23,280 --> 00:33:26,380
could we start over again?

536
00:33:32,280 --> 00:33:33,850
I'm sorry.

537
00:33:36,220 --> 00:33:38,480
Have you fallen in love with someone else?

538
00:33:46,620 --> 00:33:48,240
I see.

539
00:33:49,940 --> 00:33:52,190
Of course.

540
00:33:52,190 --> 00:33:56,520
I'm sorry for being lame. Bye.

541
00:34:07,350 --> 00:34:10,360
<i>[Yamashita]</i>

542
00:34:14,190 --> 00:34:15,730
Hello?

543
00:34:15,730 --> 00:34:19,650
<i>Sorry for calling so late. Can I see you now?</i>

544
00:34:19,650 --> 00:34:23,510
<i>Right now? I can't...</i>

545
00:34:23,510 --> 00:34:27,910
<i>Actually... I'm already here.</i>

546
00:34:27,910 --> 00:34:29,360
What?

547
00:34:29,360 --> 00:34:31,270
<i>Outside your window.</i>

548
00:34:40,020 --> 00:34:41,290
Yamashita?

549
00:34:41,290 --> 00:34:45,240
That persimmon tree's gotten a lot bigger. It's got great footholds.

550
00:34:45,240 --> 00:34:46,780
What are you doing here?

551
00:34:46,780 --> 00:34:50,130
The batteries for my remote control died, so I went to buy some.

552
00:34:50,920 --> 00:34:54,960
Then... I felt an urge to talk to you.

553
00:34:54,960 --> 00:34:56,430
About what?

554
00:34:56,430 --> 00:34:58,520
I'm not sure.

555
00:34:59,390 --> 00:35:02,390
I just really wanted to see you.

556
00:35:04,150 --> 00:35:06,180
Back in high school,

557
00:35:07,350 --> 00:35:09,540
every day

558
00:35:09,540 --> 00:35:12,670
I waited for you.

559
00:35:13,160 --> 00:35:15,730
You never noticed me, though.

560
00:35:15,730 --> 00:35:18,280
I even waited by your house.

561
00:35:19,170 --> 00:35:20,780
Really?

562
00:35:20,780 --> 00:35:23,840
You really hurt my feelings.

563
00:35:27,110 --> 00:35:29,180
I'm sorry.

564
00:35:30,250 --> 00:35:34,350
Back then, I was so focused on university exams.

565
00:35:34,350 --> 00:35:37,440
I could only see 30 centimeters ahead.

566
00:35:37,440 --> 00:35:40,260
You were a model student.

567
00:35:40,260 --> 00:35:42,120
Indeed.

568
00:35:43,410 --> 00:35:49,420
But if people saw a punk like you waiting for me,

569
00:35:49,420 --> 00:35:52,670
they would've thought I was bullied by a thug.

570
00:35:52,670 --> 00:35:56,650
Quiet! My parents are really strict!

571
00:35:56,650 --> 00:35:58,370
Sorry.

572
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:05,060
My ex-wife's dad was a handful, too.

573
00:36:05,060 --> 00:36:07,030
How so?

574
00:36:07,470 --> 00:36:09,460
He's a scary man.

575
00:36:10,170 --> 00:36:14,350
Is he an advanced version of a thug?
<i>(T/N: Mafia)</i>

576
00:36:14,350 --> 00:36:17,630
If anything, he's the opposite of that.

577
00:36:17,630 --> 00:36:19,410
The opposite?

578
00:36:19,410 --> 00:36:23,930
What is the opposite of a thug?

579
00:36:23,930 --> 00:36:25,570
What is it?

580
00:36:26,660 --> 00:36:29,000
Tell me.

581
00:36:32,360 --> 00:36:34,150
Yuri!

582
00:36:38,600 --> 00:36:42,520
Isn't it inappropriate for a teacher to personally call a student?

583
00:36:42,520 --> 00:36:45,760
I can't? I don't see why not.

584
00:36:47,260 --> 00:36:48,890
Here.

585
00:36:48,890 --> 00:36:52,420
I didn't feel comfortable to give this to you at class.
<i>[English Listening Comprehension]</i>

586
00:36:52,900 --> 00:36:56,010
I thought you could use more practice on listening English.

587
00:36:56,010 --> 00:37:00,300
I visited Sanno Seminar and saw your progress so far.

588
00:37:00,300 --> 00:37:01,930
No, I'll ask Harumi to teach me English.

589
00:37:01,930 --> 00:37:04,830
Just take it. Here.

590
00:37:06,370 --> 00:37:09,840
Why don't we walk around the area for a change?

591
00:37:12,300 --> 00:37:14,320
- Oops.
- Hey.

592
00:37:14,320 --> 00:37:16,220
Oh dear.

593
00:37:25,890 --> 00:37:30,310
Thanks for helping me to buy items for Halloween.

594
00:37:30,310 --> 00:37:33,700
No problem. Sorry for dragging you all the way to Yokohama.

595
00:37:33,700 --> 00:37:37,530
Thereâ€™s a cafÃ© nearby where waiters dressed like a feudal lord in the Sengoku period.

596
00:37:37,530 --> 00:37:38,450
Sengoku period?

597
00:37:38,450 --> 00:37:43,270
The hostess in our bar dressed up to be a feudal lord every year in Halloween.

598
00:37:43,270 --> 00:37:46,860
- I'll dressed up to be the...
- Oh?

599
00:37:46,860 --> 00:37:48,440
That's Yuri.

600
00:37:48,440 --> 00:37:50,480
Is he...

601
00:37:50,480 --> 00:37:53,730
the rumored pink boy.

602
00:38:23,040 --> 00:38:24,540
Hey,

603
00:38:26,190 --> 00:38:27,980
what is the meaning of this?

604
00:38:28,410 --> 00:38:30,060
What are you talking about?

605
00:38:30,890 --> 00:38:35,190
I don't care what you do, but if you disturb my studies next time,

606
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:38,480
I won't let you off so easy.

607
00:38:38,480 --> 00:38:41,620
What makes you so special?

608
00:38:41,620 --> 00:38:44,520
Minami High ranks the lowest. How dare you compete against us.

609
00:38:44,520 --> 00:38:50,130
Why do you even bother with me? Just focus on your own studies.

610
00:38:51,190 --> 00:38:53,460
What's the matter?

611
00:38:53,460 --> 00:38:58,850
- It's nothing. Can I ask you a question?
- Momo-chan-sensei.

612
00:38:58,850 --> 00:39:00,690
- It's been a while.
- It's been a while.

613
00:39:00,690 --> 00:39:02,920
You guys, did you come to see me?

614
00:39:02,920 --> 00:39:05,520
Of course. We're a big fan of yours. We came to help.

615
00:39:05,520 --> 00:39:07,340
Really? I'm so happy.

616
00:39:07,340 --> 00:39:10,140
Thanks to you, we're all able to get into the University of Tokyo.

617
00:39:10,140 --> 00:39:11,370
We came to repay your kindness.

618
00:39:11,370 --> 00:39:13,100
Thank you.

619
00:39:13,100 --> 00:39:15,950
I'll treat you to a meal later.

620
00:39:15,950 --> 00:39:18,250
- That's awesome!
- Great!

621
00:39:18,250 --> 00:39:22,160
Shimazaki, he's studying in the Science-3. If you have any questions, just ask him.

622
00:39:22,160 --> 00:39:25,320
- I rather ask you-
- I don't mind it. Ask me anything.

623
00:39:25,320 --> 00:39:26,850
I can help you, too.

624
00:39:29,990 --> 00:39:32,670
Yuri, do you want to join us for a meal?

625
00:39:33,300 --> 00:39:35,120
No, thanks.

626
00:39:36,880 --> 00:39:42,170
How do your students pass the college exam, while you're flirting with them?

627
00:39:44,420 --> 00:39:48,000
Motivation is the key to studies.

628
00:39:49,330 --> 00:39:51,520
It's important to get in a habit of winning.

629
00:39:52,840 --> 00:39:58,090
The thrill of solving problems shows them what is like to win.

630
00:39:58,090 --> 00:40:00,330
Most students who are aiming for the University of Tokyo,

631
00:40:00,330 --> 00:40:04,340
are top students throughout middle and high school.

632
00:40:04,340 --> 00:40:10,120
They fear the environment where they compete against other top students.

633
00:40:11,690 --> 00:40:16,830
That's why I encourage them and pamper them.

634
00:40:16,830 --> 00:40:20,580
I'm taking care of their mental health to prepare them for failure.

635
00:40:21,570 --> 00:40:25,170
So everything you do is well calculated.

636
00:40:32,920 --> 00:40:37,070
What if someone is a loser from the start?

637
00:40:39,420 --> 00:40:44,650
I believe you're the strongest person in here.

638
00:40:46,560 --> 00:40:50,570
Teacher, have you ever failed on anything?

639
00:40:54,380 --> 00:40:55,880
Never.

640
00:40:59,980 --> 00:41:04,860
Yuri, why don't you quit Sanno Seminar and join our school instead.

641
00:41:04,860 --> 00:41:08,630
None of her students made it to the University of Tokyo, right?

642
00:41:09,280 --> 00:41:12,480
- I know I'm more capable-
- But...

643
00:41:12,480 --> 00:41:14,930
Harumi is the strongest person I know.

644
00:41:15,890 --> 00:41:19,570
Probably, because she has suffered from her failure.

645
00:41:24,750 --> 00:41:29,520
She isn't calculative at all.

646
00:41:30,490 --> 00:41:32,690
Even the things related to me.

647
00:41:32,690 --> 00:41:36,270
<i>I should be the one to cheer you up today.</i>

648
00:41:36,270 --> 00:41:38,590
<i>She gets depressed more than I do.</i>

649
00:41:40,790 --> 00:41:43,810
When my old man spoke to me despicably,

650
00:41:43,810 --> 00:41:47,550
<i>Harumi suddenly scolded him.</i>

651
00:41:50,660 --> 00:41:52,300
I...

652
00:41:54,490 --> 00:41:57,790
can't imagine taking a college exam without her.

653
00:42:13,080 --> 00:42:14,950
I lost to her again.

654
00:42:14,950 --> 00:42:19,750
Teacher, I asked the graduates, but I didn't quite understand.

655
00:42:19,750 --> 00:42:21,600
Do you have a moment?

656
00:42:22,550 --> 00:42:24,760
- Teacher?
- What now?

657
00:42:26,280 --> 00:42:29,960
I'm sorry. Please ask me later.

658
00:42:44,870 --> 00:42:46,900
<i>[Tokyo Komatsu Takehara High School, The 81th Graduates Class Reunion]</i>

659
00:42:57,500 --> 00:42:59,090
What are you doing?

660
00:42:59,090 --> 00:43:00,620
Watch it!

661
00:43:00,620 --> 00:43:02,350
What's wrong?

662
00:43:02,900 --> 00:43:06,400
I've started attending dance school.

663
00:43:06,400 --> 00:43:08,600
Are you into dance?

664
00:43:09,810 --> 00:43:11,340
No.

665
00:43:11,340 --> 00:43:14,520
Oh, your cousin...

666
00:43:14,520 --> 00:43:18,300
how are things with your cousin lately?

667
00:43:18,850 --> 00:43:23,390
On our next date, I'll confess my feelings to her.

668
00:43:23,390 --> 00:43:26,140
I made a reservation for a restaurant at the Imperial Hotel.

669
00:43:26,140 --> 00:43:28,870
Are you going to propose?

670
00:43:28,870 --> 00:43:31,680
You're making me nervous.

671
00:43:31,680 --> 00:43:35,820
A proposal, huh?  Must be nice.

672
00:43:36,700 --> 00:43:38,550
Were you always this romantic?

673
00:43:38,550 --> 00:43:42,530
I realized it just recently. When people find true love,

674
00:43:42,530 --> 00:43:46,750
they become cowards. Within lies,

675
00:43:46,750 --> 00:43:49,250
there is the truth.

676
00:43:49,250 --> 00:43:50,960
- Nishioi.
- Oh.

677
00:43:52,550 --> 00:43:54,970
Hello? Saki?

678
00:43:54,970 --> 00:43:57,740
It's okay. I'm at my part-time job now.

679
00:43:57,740 --> 00:44:00,130
Part-time job?

680
00:44:04,620 --> 00:44:06,770
- Hello?
- <i>Hi, Masashi.</i>

681
00:44:06,770 --> 00:44:08,990
It's Shingen Takeda.
<i>(T/N: A feudal lord during the Sengoku period)</i>

682
00:44:08,990 --> 00:44:12,280
We're in the middle of our Halloween promotion.

683
00:44:12,280 --> 00:44:14,630
But customers aren't coming for some reason.

684
00:44:14,630 --> 00:44:17,570
<i>Masashi, come in costume! Why not bring Junko too?</i>

685
00:44:17,570 --> 00:44:20,160
A costume?

686
00:44:20,160 --> 00:44:24,370
Please show me your dance some day.

687
00:44:24,370 --> 00:44:26,330
Why won't you come?

688
00:44:26,330 --> 00:44:30,880
I'm sorry, my daughter is being loud! She has a raspy voice.

689
00:44:30,880 --> 00:44:33,180
No worries. She has an interesting voice.

690
00:44:33,180 --> 00:44:36,440
I'm telling you.  She was wearing glasses,

691
00:44:36,440 --> 00:44:40,580
but it was definitely the girl who followed you here before.

692
00:44:40,580 --> 00:44:43,660
She was walking with the pink head in Yokohama.

693
00:44:43,660 --> 00:44:45,920
<i>She was your classmate.</i>

694
00:44:45,920 --> 00:44:48,400
- Makise? Tomona Makise?
- What?

695
00:44:48,400 --> 00:44:51,170
- Yes.
- That can't be. Because...

696
00:44:51,170 --> 00:44:55,560
she didn't come to the class reunion. And why would she be with Yuri?

697
00:44:55,560 --> 00:44:58,820
I'm going to audition for the Lion King soon.

698
00:45:00,150 --> 00:45:01,770
Are you a musical dancer?

699
00:45:01,770 --> 00:45:05,040
Yes, I am.

700
00:45:05,040 --> 00:45:07,000
Makise...

701
00:45:13,380 --> 00:45:16,220
- It's been a while.
- Masashi.

702
00:45:16,220 --> 00:45:18,500
Why are you here? What about your work?

703
00:45:18,500 --> 00:45:21,650
Thank you for asking. It's going well.

704
00:45:21,650 --> 00:45:23,590
That's not what I asked.

705
00:45:23,590 --> 00:45:25,930
I need to speak with Junko real quick.

706
00:45:25,930 --> 00:45:28,570
- With Junko?
- Yes.

707
00:45:29,100 --> 00:45:30,720
- Jun.
- Oh?

708
00:45:31,450 --> 00:45:34,810
What's up? Weren't we supposed to hang out tomorrow?

709
00:45:34,810 --> 00:45:37,060
We have an important matter to discuss, and it has to be now.

710
00:45:37,060 --> 00:45:39,590
- You see-
- Wait.

711
00:45:40,110 --> 00:45:42,690
Let's talk in my room.

712
00:45:43,290 --> 00:45:45,630
- Come in.
- Thank you for having me.

713
00:45:47,270 --> 00:45:49,530
What's wrong all of a sudden?

714
00:45:49,530 --> 00:45:51,410
If it's about Yamashita,

715
00:45:51,410 --> 00:45:54,240
- I was planning on telling you-
- Yamashita?

716
00:45:56,140 --> 00:45:58,330
Not that. More importantly,

717
00:45:58,330 --> 00:46:02,490
has anyone done anything to you lately?

718
00:46:02,490 --> 00:46:05,340
Like bullying at work.

719
00:46:05,900 --> 00:46:07,930
- Bullying?
- I know

720
00:46:07,930 --> 00:46:09,980
you would never confide it to anyone.

721
00:46:09,980 --> 00:46:11,790
Are you okay?

722
00:46:12,520 --> 00:46:14,060
Masashi.

723
00:46:14,060 --> 00:46:16,220
I know you're mentally strong.

724
00:46:16,220 --> 00:46:17,950
However,

725
00:46:18,420 --> 00:46:20,760
I worry for you.

726
00:46:20,760 --> 00:46:23,480
If there's anything I can do for you...

727
00:46:24,480 --> 00:46:27,230
I'm not sure what is this about,

728
00:46:27,230 --> 00:46:29,570
but I'm all right.

729
00:46:38,060 --> 00:46:39,890
That's good to hear.

730
00:46:42,250 --> 00:46:44,080
What's the matter?

731
00:46:45,930 --> 00:46:48,510
Do you remember Tomona Makise?

732
00:46:48,510 --> 00:46:50,770
She was our high school classmate.

733
00:46:50,770 --> 00:46:53,050
- Makise?
- Yes.

734
00:46:54,460 --> 00:46:57,440
- I don't remember her.
- You know,

735
00:46:57,440 --> 00:47:00,500
the one who bullied you for a while.

736
00:47:00,500 --> 00:47:03,050
Did someone bully me?

737
00:47:03,050 --> 00:47:04,820
Are you serious?

738
00:47:04,820 --> 00:47:08,420
You really paid attention to nothing but studies.

739
00:47:10,030 --> 00:47:12,750
Does this picture refresh your memory?

740
00:47:13,710 --> 00:47:15,210
<i>[Today, I attended the wedding ceremony of my friend from high school. Tomona, may you and your husband be happy!]</i>

741
00:47:17,430 --> 00:47:20,510
What? This is Momota-sensei.

742
00:47:20,510 --> 00:47:23,290
- And she said she's twenty-seven years old.
- No, she's not.

743
00:47:23,290 --> 00:47:26,250
But this is definitely Tomona Makise.

744
00:47:26,250 --> 00:47:28,420
A girl I met at the class reunion

745
00:47:28,420 --> 00:47:31,630
uploaded Makise's wedding photo.

746
00:47:31,630 --> 00:47:33,340
No way.

747
00:47:33,340 --> 00:47:36,300
- But...
- She was always two-faced.

748
00:47:36,300 --> 00:47:38,410
I was worried about her motives.

749
00:47:38,410 --> 00:47:40,770
I'm looking into it now.

750
00:47:44,580 --> 00:47:46,820
- Hello?
- It's Nishioi.

751
00:47:46,820 --> 00:47:51,150
I looked into it, and it's spread all over the internet.

752
00:47:51,150 --> 00:47:53,850
- I'll send you the URL, so please take a look.
- Okay.

753
00:47:59,720 --> 00:48:02,130
A famous teacher of cram school specialized in the University of Tokyo.

754
00:48:02,130 --> 00:48:04,700
Tomona Momota's false educational background.

755
00:48:04,700 --> 00:48:06,930
<i>[Yikes... Is Momo-chan-sensei going to get fired?]</i>

756
00:48:08,000 --> 00:48:09,450
This can't be.

757
00:48:09,450 --> 00:48:11,010
<i>[Divorced twice at her age? It must be her personality issue.]</i>

758
00:48:11,010 --> 00:48:12,590
<i>[Doesn't matter if she's good at teaching. She lied about her academic history. She's sure to be fired.]</i>

759
00:48:12,590 --> 00:48:14,630
<i>[33? She's a grannie. And divorced twice?]</i>

760
00:48:14,630 --> 00:48:15,890
